description: Leaders of Australia, India, Japan and the United States announced plans for new security initiatives in the Indian Ocean, when outgoing President Joe Biden hosted counterparts from the Quad grouping established due to shared concerns about China.
title: Indo-Pacific leaders expand maritime security cooperation at Biden’s farewell summit

description: A former Florida sheriff's deputy was arrested for manslaughter in connection with the accidental shooting death of his girlfriend, authorities said.
title: Former Florida deputy who says he accidentally shot girlfriend while 'dry-firing' gun arrested for manslaughter

description: The nation’s wealthy opened their wallets in August with a focus on election season, donating millions to the super PACs backing Vice President Kamala Harris, former President Donald Trump and Democrats and Republicans throughout the country, according to monthly reports filed with the Federal Election Commission on Friday.
title: Billionaires poured millions of dollars into presidential super PACs in August

description: Vice President Kamala Harris' campaign on Saturday said they'd accepted an invitation to participate in a second debate with former President Donald Trump.
title: Harris accepts invitation for second potential debate in October

description: The Federal Bureau of Investigation boarded a vessel managed by the same company whose cargo ship caused the collapse of the Francis Scott Key Bridge, according to a statement published Saturday.
title: FBI board vessel managed by company whose ship caused Baltimore bridge collapse

description: The NYPD on Friday released body-worn camera footage from a weekend shooting at a Brooklyn subway station that started as a confrontation between police and an apparent fare-beater who they have said charged at officers with a knife.
title: NYPD releases bodycam footage of police shooting at Brooklyn subway platform

description: The Securities and Exchange Commission has asked a federal judge to sanction Elon Musk if he continues to violate the court’s order to appear for a deposition in a probe of his 2022 Twitter acquisition.
title: SEC says Elon Musk should be sanctioned if he keeps dodging Twitter depositions

description: CNN's Alisyn Camerota announced that her husband, Tim Lewis, died in July, two years after he was diagnosed with stage 4 pancreatic cancer.
title: CNN's Alisyn Camerota announces death of husband 2 years after pancreatic cancer diagnosis

description: Sean "Diddy" Combs is currently being held at the Metropolitan Detention Center in New York City, joining a list of high-profile inmates including Ghislaine Maxwell, R. Kelly, Martin Shkreli, and Sam Bankman-Fried. NBC’s Yasmin Vossoughian shares a look inside the harsh condition of this detention center.
title: Inside the detention center where Sean ‘Diddy’ Combs is being held

description: UC Berkeley’s Golden Bears are embracing the “woke” label as a rallying cry this football season, turning what was meant to be an insult from rivals into a meme.
title: Cal Golden Bears fans are poking fun at 'woke' jabs from Southern schools

description: An Israeli airstrike took out a top Hezbollah commander who was behind the infamous 1983 Beirut bombings at the U.S. Embassy and the marine barracks. It comes after members of the terror group were targeted in a series of attacks on their pagers and walkie talkies. NBC’s Keir Simmons reports for TODAY.
title: Top Hezbollah commander killed in Israeli airstrike in Beirut

description: Kamala Harris is targeting women, among other groups, in North Carolina, as GOP gubernatorial candidate Mark Robinson is embroiled in a fresh scandal.
title: Harris campaign seizes on suburban women as a key part of its North Carolina strategy

description: The Arizona Supreme Court ruled Friday that roughly 98,000 Arizonans whose voter registration status was in limbo will be able to participate in the full ballot in November.
title: Arizona Supreme Court decides nearly 100,000 voters will get full ballot access after clerical error

description: South Carolina put inmate Freddie Owens to death Friday as the state restarted executions after an unintended 13-year pause because prison officials couldn’t get the drugs needed for lethal injections.
title: South Carolina restarts executions after 13 years

description: Travis King, the U.S. soldier who ran across the Demilitarized Zone and into North Korea last year, was sentenced Friday to a prison term that amounts to the time he has already served.
title: U.S. soldier who crossed into North Korea sentenced to time served

description: A Texas couple was sentenced to more than a decade in prison each Friday after their pit bulls got loose and killed an 81-year-old man last year, the Bexar County District Attorney’s Office said.
title: Texas couple sentenced to prison after pit bulls killed 81-year-old man

description: A college student allegedly scratched a racial slur onto another student's body at Gettysburg College in Pennsylvania, officials said.
title: 'Pretty disgusted': Students react to racial attack

description: A California firefighter was arrested on suspicion of arson in a series of small fires that burned in wine country in recent weeks, officials said Friday.
title: California firefighter accused of setting fires in wine country
